<br>
And careful I was for 5 seasons. I got a bunch of my spells and planned ahead and budgeted my money carefully. I put enough aside for Gate, then Invisibility, hoping I'd be able to use them to stay safe, when needed. <br>
<br>
I leveled slowly, hoping to get the most of my 5 &quot;free&quot; levels where I couldn't be PKd. I got a few pieces of my quest armour. I did some tailoring and sharpening of weapons (was up to 27 in tailoring at level 5) and just had fun. But, of course, the day happened when I hit 6, even as hard as I might try to stay 5 (while still working on my quest armour. It was difficult as all the mobs I required to face were even cons if not harder)<br>
<br>
So.. ding 6.  I gated back to Felwithe, thinking I'd be safer there, and spent my practice points and invested in some gems. <br>
<br>
I headed back out to the Faydark when an 8+ druid and a 12 cleric pounced on me just outside of Felwithe, in the pass to the Faydark.  I retreated back towards Felwithe but was snared. I tried to gate, but the cleric stunned me.  I was almost dead, but as luck would have it, snare wore off and I managed to zone back into Felwithe.<br>
<br>
But, of course, I wasn't quite safe there, so I cast gate again.<br>
<br>
Your spell fizzles.<br>
<br>
Gah! No! Booo!...<br>
<br>
I was hurt (8% health or so) but tried walking into the city. I got slain by the druid on the bridge. He nuked me.<br>
<br>
Ah well. It's part of the game. I ran back to try and get my things before they were all taken. I had a bunch of things in nodrop containers, so they were safe, but I didn't want to lose my quested armour. However .. I had little to worry about.<br>
<br>
He had nuked me a little too close to the guards. One turned and killed him on the spot. His cleric friend, obviously the wiser, had not followed me into Felwithe. <br>
<br>
So, I died, so did he, and I got to keep my stuff. Whee!<br>
<br>
I've had fun on Discord, although it's more of a diversion than anything. I won't miss it when it goes offline. Just thought I'd share a little story there =)<br>
<br>
Over and out, <br>
Sibyl / Lana. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
